Hi guys, i'm searching for some help where i'm stuck. I have a "form" which needs to be filled in and submit (POST) to the API, but now my question is : What do i need to do when my app hasn't internet connection (or poor connection) ? ( I also want to save the current filled in data from the user when the POST request fails) Any help ?
<@U055GGAHS>: Do you have ideas on that last part?
I have used mapdb for exactly that in an app
just used an on disk queue

so I did 
incoming data -> queue on disk
notify new data -> service check internet -> has internet, upload
then you can monitor network changes and if a network change happens and your queue isn’t empty you can initiate your new data callback
so basically two systems only connected by the queue on disk
